    {
      "_id": "0000000000000005",
      "flags": {},
      "name": "Demonic Possession",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/mystery-man.png",
      "data": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>One humanoid that the pishacha can see within 5 feet of it must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or be possessed by the pishacha; the pishacha then disappears, and the target is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.tUYvSkhggFcMpVw5]{incapacitated} and loses some control of its body, succumbing to a random short-term madness (see the System Reference Document 5.1) each round for 3d6 rounds. At the end of the 3d6 rounds, the pishacha becomes dormant within the body.<br>While possessing a victim, the pishacha attempts to seize control of the body again every 1d4 hours. The target must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or succumb to another 3d6 round period of random short-term madness. Even if the target succeeds, it is still possessed. If the target is still possessed at the end of a long rest, it must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or gain a long-term madness.<br>While possessing a victim, the pishacha can’t be targeted by any attack, spell, or other effect, except those that can turn or repel fiends, and it retains its alignment, Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma. It otherwise uses the possessed target’s statistics, but doesn’t gain access to the target’s knowledge, class features, or proficiencies.<br>The possession lasts until the body drops to 0 hp, the pishacha ends it as a bonus action, or the pishacha is turned or forced out by an effect like the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.TkJ8Wtg1L7TZtspm]{dispel evil and good} spell. The pishacha can also be forced out if the victim eats a bowl of rice that has been cooked in holy water. When the possession ends, the pishacha reappears in an unoccupied space within 5 feet of the body.<br>The target is immune to possession by the same pishacha for 24 hours after succeeding on the initial saving throw or after the possession ends.",
          "chat": "",
          "unidentified": ""
        },
